WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:03.369
[cheers and applause]

00:00:03.402 --> 00:00:06.172
<i> [light piano music]</i>

00:00:06.205 --> 00:00:11.144
[telephone ringing]

00:00:11.177 --> 00:00:13.246
- Answer that damn telephone.

00:00:13.279 --> 00:00:14.881
- Who's calling?

00:00:14.914 --> 00:00:17.817 align:end position:100%
- We won't know unless you
answer the telephone.

00:00:17.850 --> 00:00:22.055
That is how the telephone works.

00:00:24.623 --> 00:00:26.192 line:0%
<i> - Uh, Ms. Jackson, a moment.</i>

00:00:26.225 --> 00:00:28.227 align:end position:100%
I was speaking to a colleague at
Bell Laboratories.

00:00:28.260 --> 00:00:30.463 align:end position:100%
He said they are looking for
bright young minds,

00:00:30.496 --> 00:00:32.098 align:start size:78% position:22%
outside-the-box thinkers.

00:00:32.131 --> 00:00:34.167
- Really? I've been mapping out
this idea

00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:36.502
for a phone line module that
indicates a caller's name

00:00:36.535 --> 00:00:39.606
when the telephone rings.

00:00:41.073 --> 00:00:42.575 align:start size:66% position:34%
- Okay, Ray Bradbury,

00:00:42.608 --> 00:00:44.710
save that for your science
fiction novels.

00:00:44.743 --> 00:00:47.614 align:end position:100%
They're looking for
practical applications.

00:00:53.085 --> 00:00:55.788 line:0%
<i> - Sometimes, to realize a
 dream,</i>

00:00:55.821 --> 00:00:59.058 line:0%
<i> the only voice worth
 listening to is your own.</i>

00:00:59.091 --> 00:01:01.761
- ITT is working on a go
anywhere phone,

00:01:01.794 --> 00:01:04.064
but we--we've
got nothing.

00:01:06.899 --> 00:01:11.037
- What if we had a display that
informs you who's calling?

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:12.405
- What is your name?

00:01:12.438 --> 00:01:14.407
- Dr. Shirley Ann Jackson.

00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:17.243 align:start position:0%
- Well, Ms. Dr. Shirley Ann
Jackson,

00:01:17.276 --> 00:01:20.546 align:start position:0%
I'd say you've been dipping into
your own medicine bag.

00:01:20.579 --> 00:01:22.615
[laughter]

00:01:22.648 --> 00:01:24.550
<i> [light piano music]</i>

00:01:24.583 --> 00:01:26.752
[telephone rings]

00:01:26.785 --> 00:01:28.754 align:start position:0%
- Who could possibly be
calling at this hour?

00:01:28.787 --> 00:01:30.323
- Wouldn't it be great to know?

00:01:30.356 --> 00:01:31.757
- It would.
- [scoffs]

00:01:31.790 --> 00:01:34.227 align:end position:100%
Well, tell that to my bosses
down at the lab.

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:35.962 align:start size:75% position:25%
They won't listen to me.

00:01:35.995 --> 00:01:38.698 align:start position:0%
- I'm telling you, you believe
in yourself,

00:01:38.731 --> 00:01:41.634
they ain't got no choice but to
believe in you.

00:01:41.667 --> 00:01:44.904
<i> [laughter]</i>

00:01:49.608 --> 00:01:51.744 line:0%
- Calling line identification
presentation

00:01:51.777 --> 00:01:53.579 line:0%
with an analog
system interface.

00:01:53.612 --> 00:01:56.749
- Calling line identification.

00:01:56.782 --> 00:01:58.684 align:start size:66% position:34%
Now I've seen it all.

00:01:58.717 --> 00:02:00.219
- So if your mother-in-law
calls, you don't have to answer.

00:02:00.252 --> 00:02:02.889
[applause]

00:02:02.922 --> 00:02:05.291
<i> - From executive producers
 Pharrell Williams</i>

00:02:05.324 --> 00:02:09.395
<i> and Oprah Winfrey comes the
 true story of one woman's</i>

00:02:09.428 --> 00:02:12.331
<i> struggle to change our world.</i>

00:02:12.364 --> 00:02:16.636
<i> Starring Jazmyn Simon as
 Shirley Ann Jackson</i>

00:02:16.669 --> 00:02:19.172
<i> With Ray Wise and Frank Clem</i>

00:02:19.205 --> 00:02:22.408
<i>in the studio-mandated roles of
 white savior...</i>

00:02:22.441 --> 00:02:25.311 align:start position:0%
- This is going to make those
telemarketers think twice

00:02:25.344 --> 00:02:27.380 align:start position:0%
about interrupting America's
family dinner.

00:02:27.413 --> 00:02:30.216 align:end position:100%
- And make us very, very
rich men.

00:02:30.249 --> 00:02:32.351
[laughter]

00:02:32.384 --> 00:02:35.421
[telephone ringing]

00:02:40.826 --> 00:02:42.361
<i> [cheers and applause]</i>

00:02:42.394 --> 00:02:44.430 align:end position:100%
- You know, if E equals M-C
squared,

00:02:44.463 --> 00:02:46.365 align:end position:100%
then I should be able
to cook this at 400 degrees

00:02:46.398 --> 00:02:48.100 align:end position:100%
for 27 minutes and it not
be dried.

00:02:48.133 --> 00:02:50.403 align:end position:100%
I don't really know
what's going on.

00:02:50.436 --> 00:02:52.004 align:start position:0%
- It--it...

00:02:52.037 --> 00:02:53.239 align:start size:72% position:28%
- I don't know, Morris.

00:02:53.272 --> 00:02:56.976
I just--
- We need to pray on it.

00:02:57.009 --> 00:03:00.546 align:start position:0%
Dear, Lord, please un-dry the
chicken just, uh,

00:03:00.579 --> 00:03:03.816 align:start position:0%
add some moisture deep, deep
into the thigh meat.

00:03:03.849 --> 00:03:05.318 align:start size:41% position:59%
- Yes, Jesus.

00:03:05.351 --> 00:03:08.020 align:start position:0%
- Season the--the vegetables
with your blessings

00:03:08.053 --> 00:03:09.386 align:start position:0%
and some extra salt.

